* ''Napoleon on the Nile: Soldiers, Artists, and the Rediscovery of Egypt'', [http://arthistory.about.com/od/from_exhibitions/ig/Napoleon-on-the-Nile/Joseph--1874.htm Art History].
* [http://www.ancientegypt.co.uk/ Ancient Egypt]<U+2014>maintained by the [[British Museum]], this site provides a useful introduction to Ancient Egypt for older children and young adolescents
* [http://www.digitalegypt.ucl.ac.uk/ Digital Egypt for Universities.] Outstanding scholarly treatment with broad coverage and cross references (internal and external). Artifacts used extensively to illustrate topics.
* [http://www.ancient-egypt-priests.com/ Priests of Ancient Egypt] In-depth-information about Ancient Egypt's priests, religious services and temples. Much picture material and bibliography. In English and German.
